<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 11:26AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Locally intense snow showers expected this afternoon and early
this evening...
Locally intense snow showers and/or snow bands are expected to
develop by mid-afternoon, and move south-southeast near and along
the Continental Divide into parts of southwest Montana before
ending this evening. Within these snow showers and snow bands,
expect visibility to be reduced to one-half mile or less at
times, with roads possibly become slushy or briefly snow-covered.
If traveling through these areas, expect rapidly changing
conditions near and within these showers.</description>
